<!-- Brand Story 2: text left, image right -->
<section class="about-story">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-story-grid">
      <div class="about-story-text reveal">
        <span class="section-label">From Nothing</span>
        <h2>Ten square metres in London</h2>
        <p>MUNLER was not born in a studio or a boardroom. It was born in a ten square metre room in London, where we were living at the time. We were twenty eight and twenty four. We left a career behind and put everything into this idea, in conditions that were anything but comfortable.</p>
        <p>That small room was the whole point. MUNLER came out of scarcity, out of the will to build something lasting from very little. We are partners in life as well as in work, and we built it together, from that first room.</p>
        <p>To make mirrors properly, we went looking for people who still cared about making things properly. We spoke with manufacturers across the world and chose only those who could meet our standard. We were never interested in making another mirror, we wanted to make the one that had not been made yet.</p>
        <p>The name is personal. It is ours, kept deliberately quiet, a signature rather than a spotlight.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-story-img reveal">
        <img src="https://munler.co.uk/cdn/shop/files/Gemini_Generated_Image_xskxeuxskxeuxskx.png" alt="The Solenne Mirror, MUNLER">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

